context: Another popular event held in <a2_0>February<a2_0/>, which is early <a0_0>spring<a0_0/> in Tucson, is the Fiesta de los Vaqueros, or <a1_0>rodeo week<a1_0/>, founded by winter visitor, <a3_0>Leighton Kramer<a3_0/>. While at its heart the Fiesta is a sporting event, it includes what is billed as "the world's largest non-mechanized parade". The Rodeo Parade is a popular event as most schools give <a4_0>two rodeo days off<a4_0/> instead of Presidents Day. The exception to this is Presidio High (a non-public charter school), which doesn't get either. Western wear is seen throughout the city as corporate dress codes are cast aside during the Fiesta. The Fiesta de los Vaqueros marks the beginning of the rodeo season in the United States.
